  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chop your chicken into small chunks, pop them into a large mixing bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Whisk your egg and add ½ of it to your chicken along with the milk, white pepper, Shaoxing wine and 1 teaspoon of salt. Give it a good mix and pop it in the fridge."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a separate mixing bowl, combine all the ingredients for seasoning the chicken. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chop your onion into pieces, mince your garlic, red chilli and thinly slice your spring onions. Pop them into a bowl and set them aside for later."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a separate mixing bowl, mix the potato starch with the self-raising flour."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the marinated chicken pieces to the flour mix. Then, one by one, shake the excess flour off the chicken and add the remaining flour mix to the chicken."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour 1.5 litres of oil into your wok on medium heat, pop a chopstick in and if bubbles emerge, your oil is ready. Place half your chicken pieces into the oil and fry until lightly golden. Place them on a paper-lined tray and deep fry the remaining chicken pieces."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Repeat, and deep fry the chicken pieces again (this time until crispy and golden)."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add a glug of oil to a wok, then fry your prepped veg from earlier. Add your crispy chicken and the seasoning mix. Give it a good toss until everything is combined and the chicken is evenly coated in seasoning."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Tuck in and enjoy!"
    }
  ],
